physical_examinations.relevant_findings: General: Alert and oriented x3, no acute distress; HEENT: No scleral icterus, mucous membranes moist; Cardiovascular: Regular rate and rhythm, no murmurs, gallops, or rubs; Pulmonary: Clear to auscultation bilaterally, no wheezes, rhonchi, or rales; Abdominal: Not specified; GU: No inguinal or femoral hernias; DRE: Normal tone, no gross or occult blood, no tenderness; Extremities: Warm, well perfused, no edema/cyanosis/clubbing, 2+ distal pulses.
